From 1501daf7c7e5bd4083d48db976d9fabc7e72e8e4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 14:05:12 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] net: ethernet: tc956x: Add Qualcomm platform driver
 support

The TC956X PCIe Ethernet bridge (QPS615) requires SoC-specific
initialization on Qualcomm platforms that is not handled by the
generic PCI driver. Add a dedicated platform driver file,
tc956x_qcom.c, to manage this hardware configuration. This
requires stubbing out the existing platform functions.

The Qualcomm platform driver handles:
 - PHY reset control via TC956X GPIO or SoC GPIO descriptor
 - PHY power supply management
 - Pinctrl default state selection
 - Wake-on-LAN IRQ configuration
 - Suspend/resume hooks that gate PHY power when WoL is inactive

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Qualcomm specific platform logic]
Signed-off-by: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/Makefile  |   4 +
 .../net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956x_qcom.c | 296 ++++++++++++++++++
 .../net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956xmac.h   |   4 +-
 .../ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956xmac_main.c  |  39 ---
 4 files changed, 302 insertions(+), 41 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 drivers/net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956x_qcom.c

